The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Mohali Test on
                                                                                                                                                                                           Mohali Test on
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The England and Wales Cricket Board (ECB) security adviser, Reg Dickason, England Cricket managing director Hugh Morris, and Sean Morris, the chief executive of the Professional Cricketers Association, on Wednesday approved the security arrangements for the second Test in Mohali starting on December 19, according to an ECB release.         
	After inspecting the arrangements put in place by the Board of Control for Cricket in India and the Punjab Cricket Association, Hugh said: We have nothing but praise for the efforts of everyone at Mohali.                                                                                                                          
